OL,3,C'They feel safer in prison': Homeless
OL,4,Cpeople turning to crime to secure
OL,5,Cshelter
OL,7,FHowever on Thursday, Ni Chuilin
OL,8,Frejected this: "The statement that
OL,9,Feveryone was offered a bed is not
OL,10,Fcorrect.
OL,12,F"The night in question, I was out on
OL,13,Fthe streets doing outreach. There were
OL,14,Fpeople who tried to access a bed from
OL,15,F9 o'clock that morning, were told to
OL,16,Fring back at 5, they kept ringing
OL,17,Fthroughout the day, rang back at 1
OL,18,Fminute or 2 minutes past 5, and the
OL,19,Femergency beds, accommodation were all
OL,20,Fgone."
